protocols.description:
Configuration to allow/forbid playing the stream via various protocols. 
- If the `whitelist` option is set to 'true', the server allows a playback only for listed protocols;
- If the `whitelist` option is set to 'false', the server forbids a playback for listed protocols;
- Server allows a playback for all the protocols by default.

post.description:
Just parse and validate config, nothing is saved.

Provide JSON structure or plain text.

Take a look at this example:
```
curl -d 'http 80; stream mystream { input ""; }' \
  -H 'Content-Type: text/plain' \
  -sS http://login:pass@localhost:8080/streamer/api/v3/config | jq
{
  "col": 34,
  "config": {
    "http": [
      "80"
    ],
    "streams": [
      {
        "inputs": [
          {
            "url": ""
          }
        ],
        "name": "mystream"
      }
    ]
  },
  "detail": "",
  "error": "bad_url",
  "line": 1,
  "path": [
    "streams",
    0,
    "inputs",
    0,
    "url",
    "input_url"
  ]
}
```

You can see that it is possible to fix error on column 34 where bad, empty url was saved.

text/plain.example:
http 80;

stream mystream {
  input udp://239.0.0.1:1234;
  transcoder vb=2048k ab=64k;
}
